name: Kokkino's café (though window simply says "cafe")
directions: At the back. Locking door. One bathroom for whole cafe.
comment: Owner is very neighbourly and friendly. Probably be able to use bathroom without buying if you ask. But if you can swing 2$ for a coffee, pls do. Local business, community minded.

name: Circle k

name: St Olaf College Boe Chapel
directions: In the Undercroft, by the men's stall restrooms and the water fountain.
comment: There are two single stall restrooms.

name: Rise N Shine cafe
comment: It's a restaurant and there is a sign that the restroom is for paying customers only

name: Lokal
directions: Downstairs to the right
comment: One room with urinal and toilet.

name: Labyrinth Games & Puzzles
directions: Two unisex, single occupancy.

name: Bilbo Baggins Global Restaurant
directions: Turn to the left to go into the bar area of the restaurant, walk all the way to the end of the bar and you'll see a door with a restroom sign on it on your right.
comment: As far as I can tell, you don't have to be a paying customer, but I have only visited the restaurant on a day when it was being staffed by one person for some reason. The restroom itself is single-stall and has both a toilet and a urinal.

name: Peace Zone
directions: Go through the Peace Zone entrance. It's only open three days a week and you might have to seem interested in Peace Zone for a second but it's a good restroom.
comment: Just act interested in Peace Zone if anyone questions you. It's a mental health service.

name: Sequoya Library
directions: Near the large meeting rooms and the DVDs. If you enter on the parking lot side, it's to the left (the gendered restrooms and the water fountain are to the right).

name: Main Library
directions: All floors

name: Great Lakes Coffee
directions: Both restrooms are non-gendered. Choose either "better lighting" or "better water pressure." You do not need to request a key.
comment: I believe you have to be a paying customer but I'm also relatively certain that if you tell a staff member that you need a safe restroom, you'll be good to go.

name: Costco wholesale
directions: Down the hall past the Food Court. Just past the main bathrooms
comment: It is the family bathroom

name: Coe College, Lower Gage
directions: Behind the cafeteria in Lower Gage. Take the set of stairs by the art sculpture into the side door to go directly there.
comment: Works for students and staff, and "visitors" to the college.

name: kleine Freiheit
comment: It's a coffee shop, you should buy something.

name: Community College of Baltimore County Essex
directions:
There are several.
Library: straight through the entrance, turn left in the lobby, first door on your right.
Mathematics and Science Hall (MASH): there are eight of these restrooms in the building and every one is located in the central hallway across from the elevator on every floor.
comment: You technically have to be a student to use them and we do have campus security, but if you're college age and you look like you belong there, they probably won't bother you. There is a considerable amount of walking involved to get to each bathroom, so if you have mobility issues or it's an emergency, this may not be the best option.

name: El Mirasol
street: 140 E Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264
comment: Two ungendered bathrooms, both single occupant.

name: Society Cafe
directions: Down stairs inside
comment: Supposedly for paying customers, but often busy enough that you'll get in fine

name: Society Cafe
directions: Down stairs inside
comment: Supposedly for paying customers, but often busy enough that you'll get in fine

name: Kinley's House Coffee & Tea
comment: They're right in front of the far right entrance.

name: Kinley's House Coffee & Tea
comment: They're right in front of the far right entrance.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two bathrooms available, turn left upon entering store.
comment: Restroom on the left has a urinal

name: SmARTroom

comment: Just come in and ask to use the restroom.

name: Siberian Cat Cafe
directions: Back of cafe, in the cat room - bathroom is large, home-style bathroom. Cats are Siberians, so shouldn't irritate allergies too much.
comment: I don't think you have to be a paying customer, but it is further into the building, so it might not be a bad idea.

name: Talihina Public Library
directions: Enter the library, take double doors on your left, restroom in hallway. Single stall unisex.

name: Bareburger
directions: Go towards the back of the restaurant and make a right. Bathrooms are in the little hallway.

name: Red Moon Studio
directions: Through entry way, to the right.
comment: Business Only open for classes and performances. Two bathrooms - anyone can use.

name: Conoco Gas Station
directions: Go in turn right - it's the only bathroom
comment: Paying customer only so buy gas or gum

name: Aldi
directions: To the right of the cash registers, straight through front doors.
comment: Don't have to be paying customer.

name: Target
directions: Family restroom next to the gendered restrooms

name: Rawr Sushi
directions: In back on left

name: Lighthouse Cinema
directions:
On left at entrance before ticket desk. 
To get downstairs to second bathroom use lift. You'll likely need a cinema ticket to get downstairs.
comment:
Bathroom on ground floor and bathroom on floor -3. 
Each has a unisex room with sinks and 3 individual cubicles marked man, woman wheelchair.
Wheelchair stall has very narrow door, not accessible to all wheelchairs.

name: UCD arts and sciences
directions: Near the parking elevators
comment: Building closes at 6pm

name: Starbucks
directions: Two restrooms available. Single stall each.

name: target
directions: next to the pharmacy
comment: family restroom/unisex

name: Target
directions:
To the left of the pharmacy
If you enter next to the the Starbucks, continue straight until you pass the makeup, and go left through the over the counter medicine shelves, but you should be able to see the pharmacy sign when you enter.
If you enter next to the clothes/accessories, take a right after you pass the clearance area and then continue forwards until you can go left through the makeup.  Once get to the Pharmacy it'll be to your left.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: "family restroom" is single stall/non-gendered. With the gendered bathrooms - walk through produce and turn left and follow signs.
comment: Lift handle up to go in! Sometimes it feels locked when pushed down.

name: Lilliput Families
directions: Lilliput sign is small.  Turn down drive and follow to the back.  On the right side.
comment: Just ask for the restroom.  You are welcome.

name: Adelphi Manhattan Center School of Social Work
directions: When you enter the campus, the bathrooms are the first left right next to the entrance doors. The gender-neutral bathroom is along the wall, so you'll need to turn around at the end of the hallway to see it.
comment: You'll need to show ID on the first floor to get a visitor's pass to enter the building, and you'll need to sign in at the Adelphi front desk. If you're an Adelphi student, you can use your student ID for both checkpoints. The Adelphi campus is a safe space, so no worries about harassment.

name: Hoyt Hall, University of Wyoming
directions: Second and third floors have unisex, private bathrooms and there usually aren't many people there anyway

name: Pacifier
directions: Out the back door of the store, into the main building.

name: Richfield Township Hall
directions: Just inside the front door.

name: Troy Miami-County Public Library
directions: Across from the circulation desk
comment: Two 'gendered' bathrooms, but they are open to declared genders. One family single stall bathroom.

name: Pizza Hut
directions: As soon as you walk in, to the right in a short, dim hallway
comment: Do not have to be a paying customer

name: NYU Tisch School of the Arts
directions: They're on the 9th, 10th, and 11th floors. Tisch building is also a safe space to use the gendered bathroom that you assign with.
comment: You must be an NYU student.

name: The Admiral's Cup
directions: Three single stall bathrooms, the one that's unisex is on the left
comment: Don't have to be a paying customer, but it can get really crowded during the summer so there might be a long line

name: Funky Monkey Nite Club
directions: Across from the dance floor, just to the left of the bar
comment: There's not usually a cover to get in. Their bathroom policy is posted on the wall in the restrooms and the staff is super friendly and helpful.

name: Else's
directions: At the back, down a tiny hallway on the right.
comment: Fairly small and crowded restaurant/bar, but everyone is at tables. Pretending you're looking for someone/a group of people is the easiest way to get through the room without waiting to be seated.

name: Cunningham Memorial Library
directions: On the first floor in the southeast corner of the building. Two gender-neutral single stalls

name: Starbucks

comment: It requires a code to get in. Sometimes they will just give it to you, sometimes you have to buy something.

name: Cha Shu Bubble Tea
directions: Straight past the counter to the back
comment: For customers, staff is very nice, lots of inexpensive drinks and snacks

name: Walters Hall - SUNY-ESF
directions: First floor of Walters Hall on left side of elevator.
comment: Building locks after 6:00 PM and opens at 6:00 AM. Closed on weekends.

name: Amplify Hair Studio
comment: This is in a hair studio, so you'd have to be there for some reason, though they do sell hair products, as well. You could go in to check out the products and ask to use the bathroom. It's small but friendly staff.

name: Westfield Wheaton
directions: Second floor, by Costco. Next to Panda Express.

name: Consider it JoyBaking
directions: Employee will show you
comment:
Just ask :)
We are a very small, friendly business.

name: Harris School (UChicago)
directions:
Enter via the main entrance (on the right behind the bus shelter, not through the courtyard). There is a small alcove immediately to the left of the front door with two all gender, single stall restrooms. 
Accessible directions: The accessible entrance is behind the building (on the parking lot side). From there, head straight through the building, past the cafe, to the front lobby with the staffed security desk. The alcove is on your right.
